# TSan suppressions for pool-of-threads
# False positives from crossbeam-epoch's epoch-based garbage collection.
# TSan cannot model epoch reclamation — it sees concurrent free + read on
# the garbage queue inside Global::collect and flags it as a data race.
# The epoch counter guarantees the object is only freed after all threads
# have advanced past the epoch where it was retired.
# See: https://github.com/crossbeam-rs/crossbeam/issues/589

# Global::collect runs on multiple threads. One thread frees garbage-bag
# nodes while another reads them from the concurrent queue. Epoch ordering
# guarantees these operations are safe, but TSan sees raw read+free.
race:crossbeam_epoch::internal::Global::collect
